    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm working on a research paper and i think i keep using passive voice too much. can u help me identify it and show me how to fix it? like if i have a sentence like \"the data was collected by the researchers\" how do i make it better?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The passive voice can be a sneaky one, but don't worry, I'm here to help you identify and fix it. You're right, \"the data was collected by the researchers\" is a classic example of passive voice. To make it more active, you can rephrase it to \"the researchers collected the data.\" This change makes the subject (the researchers) the doer of the action, rather than the recipient of the action (the data). \n\nBy doing so, you're not only making the sentence more active, but also more engaging and easier to read. You can also try to identify the passive voice in your sentences by asking yourself: \"Who or what is performing the action?\" or \"Is the focus on the action or the result?\" If it's the result, you might be using passive voice.",
